text: I‚Äôm really confused by all these ‚Äúclapbacks‚Äù. If I didn‚Äôt know who TS was I wouldn‚Äôt know a thing about Kayla. I dont consider myself a swiftie. I‚Äôm not a diehard for her. At most I‚Äôm happy that she‚Äôs found a relationship that makes her feel so giddy in love and so proud of her man and life after years of trying to find the right one. But I am a fan of her music because it brings me back to the times in my life where I was on the same journey. That‚Äôs what lyricism is. Everyone can feel betrayed and belittled by ‚Äúfriends‚Äù (even if unintended - which I agree Charlie‚Äôs song was). Everyone can misunderstand but still are allowed to feel the way they feel). Everyone‚Äôs compared themselves of the girl/guy before. Take away what you know about TS life and you see that these are REAL human experiences and thoughts. Kayla liking shady stuff about Taylor & Travis is EXPLICIT but writing songs about experiences and emotions around relationships and friendships is IMPLICIT. And while we forget what posts Kayla liked because she‚Äôs not as big as her, we‚Äôre all quick to label Taylor as a bully for using her own life and feelings for music on her platform? Can we just like her music and support her journey without knowing everyone single connection she has to everyone else?
